      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush and the Debates</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Aides to Gov. George W. Bush are objecting to the three debates that have been proposed by the Commission on Presidential Debates. The aides said they did not want to commit to three debates on prime-time television and wanted a more relaxed, conversational format. They also are concerned about the site of one debate -- near the John F. Kennedy Library in Boston.</p>
        <p>Article, Page A18.</p>
      </block>
